This course introduces Generalized Linear Latent Variable Models (GLLVMs), a unifying framework for advanced multivariate analysis of ecological communities. GLLVMs combine the flexibility of Generalized Linear Models with the benefits of ordination, enabling robust species association analysis, model diagnostics, and more.

Who Should Attend?

The course is designed for PhD candidates, postdocs, and researchers with basic statistical knowledge and experience with R. If you work with multivariate ecological data and want to learn statistically sound methods to analyze it, this course is for you!

What You?ll Learn:


    Fitting GLLVMs with the gllvm R-package, choosing the appropriate distribution for data.
    Formulating an appropriate GLLVM to answer a research question.
    Finding a "good" GLLVMs based on residual diagnostics and other criteria covered in the course.
    Visualizing and interpreting results from a fitted GLLVM.
    The ability to effectively communicate the results.


